ow identical uniform size and consistent latex production - 130 experimental trees with equal performance", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "DOUBLE normal yield - 1.75 liters latex/day per tree, 25 kg dry rubber vs normal production", "growing_notes": "Important foundation clone in Malaysian breeding. Part of early mother tree selections starting 1928. REMARKABLE Kerala discovery! One tree from 350 RRII-105 saplings showed exceptional performance. Published in ''Rubber Asia'' and Rubber Board magazine. Scientific study ongoing to determine if genetic mutation or cultivation technique. Could be genetic breakthrough or result of specific fertilizer use. Represents potential major advancement for Kerala rubber farming if genetics confirmed.", "availability": "LIMITED - Father Thomas operates nursery in Kerala with budwood from original tree. Farmers visiting to see trees. Patent application in process as of 2017", "sort_order": 40}], "variety_count": 41}'::jsonb,
