ighest yield variety in many Indian trials. Very productive in appropriate conditions.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 2}, {"name": "Winter Dawn", "slug": "winter-dawn", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "California breeding program, USA", "traits": "Short-day variety suited to winter production in warmer regions. Good adaptation to varied structures.", "flesh_fruit": "Good flavor and appearance. Medium to large berries.", "yield_notes": "175-245 quintals/hectare productivity range recorded in Indian trials. Good commercial yields.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 3}, {"name": "Camino Real", "slug": "camino-real", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "University of California, USA", "traits": "Short-day variety producing extended fruit in arid subtropical climates when treated appropriately. Similar pattern to Camarosa but later fruiting.", "flesh_fruit": "Good flavor and appearance. Suitable for warm-climate production.", "yield_notes": "Productive in subtropical conditions with proper cultivation methods.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 4}, {"name": "Sea Scape", "slug": "sea-scape", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "University of California, USA", "traits": "Everbearing variety not sensitive to day length. Does well in tropics according to Burgess Seed Company.", "flesh_fruit": "Large flavorful berries with attractive glossy finish. Good quality fruit.", "yield_notes": "Good everbearing production. Concentrated yields in late spring with high fall production.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "May need to be sourced from international suppliers or specialized Indian importers. Check with Kerala agricultural universities.", "sort_order": 5}, {"name": "Albion", "slug": "albion", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "University of California, US